| [inference_config.json](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Green%20AI/Models/Crop%20Disease%20Detection/inference_config.json) | < 1 KB | Class list, preprocessing params, crop map |

> **Recommended format:** `.ptl` (PyTorch Mobile Lite) — already optimised and fused for mobile. Use `.onnx` only if the team prefers ONNX Runtime.

All files are in the `logs/` folder of the training project.

---

## 3. Model Specifications

### Stage 1 — Binary Classifier (Healthy vs Diseased)

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Architecture | MobileNetV3-Large |
| Parameters | 5.4 Million |
| Input | `[1, 3, 224, 224]` (batch, RGB, H, W) |
| Output | `[1, 2]` — logits for [Diseased, Healthy] |
| Class index 0 | Diseased |
| Class index 1 | Healthy |
| Validation accuracy | **99.57%** |
| Format | FP32 trained → INT8 quantized |

### Stage 2 — Disease Classifier (13 Classes)

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Architecture | EfficientNetV2-S |
| Parameters | 20.2 Million |
| Input | `[1, 3, 224, 224]` (same as Stage 1) |
| Output | `[1, 13]` — logits for 13 disease classes |
| Test accuracy | **85.0%** (190 test images) |
| Format | FP32 trained → INT8 quantized |

### Stage 2 — Class Index Table

| Index | Class Name | Crop |
|---|---|---|
| 0 | Citrus_blossomendrot | citrus |
| 1 | Citrus_canker | citrus |
| 2 | Citrus_leafminer | citrus |
| 3 | Citrus_scab | citrus |
| 4 | Rice_brownleafspot | rice |
| 5 | Rice_falsesmut | rice |
| 6 | Rice_leafblight | rice |
| 7 | Rice_planthopper | rice |
| 8 | Sugarcane_brownspot | sugarcane |
| 9 | Sugarcane_eyespot | sugarcane |
| 10 | Sugarcane_redrot | sugarcane |
| 11 | Sugarcane_ringspot | sugarcane |
| 12 | Sugarcane_smut | sugarcane |

> **Important:** Indices are fixed and sorted alphabetically. Do not reorder.

---

## 4. Preprocessing — Must Be Exact

Both Stage 1 and Stage 2 use **identical preprocessing**. Wrong values will silently produce garbage predictions.

```
1. Load image as RGB (not BGR)
2. Resize to 224 × 224 pixels  (bilinear interpolation)
3. Convert pixels to float32, divide by 255.0  → range [0.0, 1.0]
4. Normalize each channel:
     R = (R - 0.485) / 0.229
     G = (G - 0.456) / 0.224
     B = (B - 0.406) / 0.225
5. Shape: [1, 3, 224, 224]  (batch=1, channels first)
```

These are **standard ImageNet normalization values** — any ML library will have this as a preset.

---

## 5. Inference Logic — Step by Step

```
INPUT: image (JPEG/PNG from camera), crop_type ("citrus" | "rice" | "sugarcane")

STEP 1: Preprocess image → tensor [1, 3, 224, 224]

STEP 2: Run Stage 1
  → logits = stage1_model.forward(tensor)  → shape [1, 2]
  → probs  = softmax(logits)
  → p_diseased = probs[0][0]
  → p_healthy  = probs[0][1]

STEP 3: Gate
  IF p_healthy >= 0.5:
    RETURN { result: "healthy", confidence: p_healthy × 100 }

STEP 4: Run Stage 2 (only if diseased)
  → logits = stage2_model.forward(tensor)  → shape [1, 13]
  → all_probs = softmax(logits)            → 13 values summing to 1.0

STEP 5: Filter by crop type
  → Use inference_config.json → crop_disease_map[crop_type]
    to get list of relevant class names
  → Get their indices from class_list_sorted
  → Extract only those probability values

STEP 6: Re-normalise
  → filtered_probs = filtered_probs / sum(filtered_probs)

STEP 7: Return result
  → top_class = argmax(filtered_probs)
  → disease_name = class_list_sorted[top_class_index]
  RETURN {
    result: "diseased",
    disease: disease_name,
    confidence: top_prob × 100,
    all_probabilities: { disease_name: prob, ... }
  }
```

