## 6. Platform Integration

### Android — PyTorch Mobile

```kotlin
// Dependency
implementation("org.pytorch:pytorch_android_lite:2.1.0")

// Load models (place .ptl files in assets/)
val stage1 = LiteModuleLoader.load(assetFilePath("stage1_quantized.ptl"))
val stage2 = LiteModuleLoader.load(assetFilePath("stage2_quantized.ptl"))

// Preprocess (use torchvision transforms or manual)
val inputTensor = TensorImageUtils.bitmapToFloat32Tensor(
    bitmap,
    floatArrayOf(0.485f, 0.456f, 0.406f),   // mean
    floatArrayOf(0.229f, 0.224f, 0.225f)    // std
)

// Forward pass
val outputStage1 = stage1.forward(IValue.from(inputTensor)).toTensor()
```

### iOS — LibTorch

```swift
// Dependency: add pytorch_ios pod via CocoaPods
// pod 'LibTorch-Lite', '~> 2.1.0'

// Load model
let stage1 = TorchModule.load(filePath("stage1_quantized"))
let stage2 = TorchModule.load(filePath("stage2_quantized"))

// Input: Float32 array, shape [1, 3, 224, 224], ImageNet-normalized
let inputData: [Float] = preprocessImage(uiImage)
let result = stage1.predict(image: &inputData)
```

### Offline Storage

- Bundle `.ptl` files inside the app binary (in `assets/` on Android, app bundle on iOS)
- No network call required at inference time
- [inference_config.json](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Green%20AI/Models/Crop%20Disease%20Detection/inference_config.json) should also be bundled — read class names and crop map from it, not hardcoded

