## 8. Model Update Protocol

When the AI team releases a new model version (after collecting more field data):

1. AI team provides new `.ptl` and `.onnx` files with a version tag (e.g., `v1.1`)
2. AI team also provides updated [inference_config.json](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Green%20AI/Models/Crop%20Disease%20Detection/inference_config.json) if new diseases/crops were added
3. Mobile team replaces the bundled files in the app and re-releases
4. The class index table in this document will be updated with each release

> **No code logic changes are needed** when new diseases are added to existing crops — only [inference_config.json](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Green%20AI/Models/Crop%20Disease%20Detection/inference_config.json) changes. Code changes are only required if a completely new crop type is added.

